Yep, fully aware of that.  You might note that we have never broken an RTA rule, nor do we plan on it.  This includes several dozen HoT raids when named mobs related to Doze were up, our two attempts at the Idol without using slow, dozens and dozens of times when we could have ganked a mob on a rot but didn't and our immediate removal of any non-guild, non-applicant people when we try a new rotation.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Again, if you're willing to piss off guilds by teaming, why would you hesitate to piss them off by breaking rotations? You're only after exp spots!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
